Japan with #ModernBazaar 🇯🇵🍥
 
Itadakimasu! — it’s a common Japanese phrase that means “I humbly receive.” It’s almost always used before eating to show appreciation for the food before you dig in, like the religious custom of saying grace before a meal.

With its aesthetic of beautifully presented food and the use of fresh, high-quality seasonal ingredients, it’s no wonder that Japan’s cuisine is so delicious and so highly prized by people around the world. 💕
